Russian Equity Movers: Norilsk Nickel, Rosneft, Polymetal

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-02T15:56:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/russian-equity-movers-norilsk-nickel-rosneft-polymetal-tmk.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  fell for
the first day this week, losing 2.3 percent to 1,515.89 by the
6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
slumped 2.7 percent to 1,657.25 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX),  Russia ’s biggest mining
company, slid by its most in than two weeks, losing 2.4 percent
to 7,030 rubles as nickel and copper fell in  London .  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), the country’s largest oil producer,
fell for the first day this week, losing 1.7 percent to 227.3
rubles. Crude for October delivery retreated as much as 3
percent to $86.28 a barrel in electronic trading on the  New York
Mercantile Exchange .  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a gold and silver producer,
advanced to the highest since Aug. 23, adding 1.4 percent to
625.4 rubles as the price of both metals increased.  To contact the reporter on this story:
